{"lemma":"مُحْكَمٌ","slug":"مُحْكَمٌ","root":"ح.ك.م","root_slug":"ح-ك-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ك-م","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8722"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AD%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of أَحْكَمَ (ʔaḥkama)","tags":["form-of","participle","passive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"tight, airtight, sealed"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"coherent, solid","tags":["figuratively"],"examples":[{"text":"خِطَّة مُحْكَمَة","english":"a watertight plan"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"perfect","tags":["perfect"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of أَحْكَمَ (ʔaḥkama)."},"ipa":["/muħ.kam/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8722","headword_ar":"مُحْكَمٌ","root":"Hkm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[pass. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHokamahu","text_ar":"اَحْكَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] applied to a building [&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered, firm, stable, strong, solid, compact, &c.; held to be secure from falling to pieces."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT.) ―         -b2-  And hence, A passage, or portion, of the Kur-án"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the meaning is secured"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHokima","text_ar":"اُحْكِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from change, and alteration, and peculiarization, and interpretation not according to the obvious import, and abrogation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrapN muHokamapN","text_ar":"سُورَةٌ مُحْكَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chapter"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Kur-án"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not abrogated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=yaAtu","text_ar":"الا=يَاتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHokamaAtu","text_ar":"المُحْكَمَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [see Kur iii. 5, where it is opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yaAtN muta$aAbihaAtN","text_ar":"ا=يَاتٌ مُتَشَابِهَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The portion commencing with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qulo taEaAlawoA A^atolu maA Har~ama rab~ukumo","text_ar":"قُلْ تَعَالَوْا اَتْلُ مَا حَرَّمَ رَبُّكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Kur vi. 152],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the end of the chapter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the verses that are rendered free from defect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperfection, so that the hearer thereof does not need to interpret them otherwise than according to their obvious import; such as the stories of the prophets;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that they are preserved from being susceptible of several meanings."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in iii. 5.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHokamu","text_ar":"المُحْكَمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The portion of the Kur-án called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmufaS~alu","text_ar":"المُفَصَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; because nought thereof has been abrogated: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is unequivocal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unambiguous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because its perspicuity is made free from defect, or imperfection, and it requires nothing else [to explain it]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}